<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Programming note:</strong><em> Money S=
tuff will be off tomorrow, back on Monday.</em></p><table class=3D"header" =
width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Insider trading (1)</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I assume that most people who work in =
compliance at big investment banks are good, upstanding, compliant people, =
but I also get the impression that there is a small but important minority =
who got into the compliance group because they thought it would be a good p=
lace to commit crimes? <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/c=
lick/25195151.265551/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLz=
IwMjEtMDktMjkvc2VjLXN1ZXMtaW52ZXN0bWVudC1iYW5rLWNvbXBsaWFuY2UtYW5hbHlzdC1mb=
3ItaW5zaWRlci10cmFkaW5n/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc99dff46" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: no=
ne !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bord=
er-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Oops</a>:</p><blockquote>=
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A former Goldman Sachs Group Inc. compliance a=
nalyst whose job was to help the bank prevent insider trading was himself c=
harged with insider trading by the Securities and Exchange Commission.</p><=
p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The SEC sued Jose Luis Casero Sanchez on Wednes=
day, claiming he used his position in the bank=E2=80=99s Warsaw office to a=
ccess a control room which stored confidential information on =E2=80=9Call =
pending and potential transactions in which the investment bank was involve=
d and advising clients.=E2=80=9D He made at least $471,700 in illegal tradi=
ng profits, the regulator said.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
">Look, it <em>is=C2=A0</em>a good place to commit crimes! =E2=80=9CNobody =
suspects the compliance analyst=E2=80=9D would be a funny thing to say but =
isn=E2=80=99t particularly true; I bet everyone suspects the compliance ana=
lyst. The real advantage is access to information.=C2=A0If you go to Goldma=
n and work as an investment banking analyst, you will know about the handfu=
l of mergers that you are working on, and you will certainly hear about=C2=
=A0some other mergers that your friends are working on, but there are at le=
ast vague gestures in the direction of compartmentalization and confidentia=
lity even within the firm, and anyway you=C2=A0are mostly busy on your own =
deals, not gossiping about everyone else=E2=80=99s.=C2=A0Nobody is going to=
 hand you a list of =E2=80=9Chere is every merger we are working on.=E2=80=
=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Whereas they did hand Casero Sanchez th=
at list. From <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2519=
5151.265551/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2NvbXBsYWludHMvMjAyMS9=
jb21wLXByMjAyMS0yMDMucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb71ddce8" itemprop=3D"St=
oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the SEC=E2=80=99s compla=
int</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One of Sanchez=E2=80=
=99s duties was to update the firm=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9CGrey List,=E2=80=9D w=
hich is a confidential list of public and private entities for which the fi=
rm=E2=80=99s private-side personnel possess material, nonpublic information=
.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Typically, Grey List entities are involve=
d in merger and acquisition activity and financings such as public and priv=
ate securities offerings, among other things. If an entity is on the Grey L=
ist, certain controls at the Investment Bank may be implicated, including b=
ut not limited to, surveillance of firm and client trading activities in th=
e securities of the company on the list, and the denial of certain employee=
s=E2=80=99 personal trade requests in the securities of the company on the =
list.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Grey List is maintained on =
an internal database at the Investment Bank (the =E2=80=9CConfidential Data=
base=E2=80=9D). The Confidential Database is the depository where material,=
=C2=A0nonpublic information about potential transactions involving the Inve=
stment Bank is stored. For each transaction, the Confidential Database may =
include, but is not limited to: the names of the public and private entitie=
s involved in the potential or pending transaction; the firm=E2=80=99s role=
 in the transaction; the nature of the transaction; the securities involved=
; the type of financing involved; the size of the transaction; pricing info=
rmation; the projected announcement date; and other material, nonpublic det=
ails regarding the potential transaction.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margi=
n: 16px 0;">If someone hands you the passwords to a database and is like =
=E2=80=9Chere is a comprehensive list of all the stocks that we wouldn=E2=
=80=99t want anyone to insider trade on=E2=80=9D=C2=A0=E2=80=A6=C2=A0you ca=
n see the temptation right?</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway if you=
=E2=80=99re an investment banking analyst and you work on like four deals a=
nd insider trade on all of them, there are some problems; you only have a f=
ew shots to make money and you might find yourself reaching for profits by =
buying short-dated out-of-the-money call options on merger targets, a viola=
tion of my <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2519515=
1.265551/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTgtMD=
gtMTIvdGhlLTEwLWxhd3Mtb2YtaW5zaWRlci10cmFkaW5n/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc83=
e6980" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Sec=
ond Law of Insider Trading</a>. If you=E2=80=99re a compliance analyst with=
 access to the comprehensive database of all deals, you can insider trade a=
t a more leisurely pace. From the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/25195151.265551/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJ=
lbGVhc2UvMjAyMS0yMDM/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB90035bd4" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none =
!important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-=
bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">SEC=E2=80=99s press release</=
a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Between September 2020 and =
May 2021, Sanchez allegedly abused that position of trust by trading on at =
least 45 events involving the investment bank=E2=80=99s clients based on th=
e investment bank=E2=80=99s material, nonpublic information. To avoid detec=
tion, Sanchez allegedly traded in multiple U.S.-based brokerage accounts he=
ld in the name of one of his parents=E2=80=94Jose Luis Casero Abellan and M=
aria Isabel Sanchez Gonzalez =E2=80=94and, in most instances, also refraine=
d from placing large trades and made only modest profits. The complaint all=
eges that Sanchez generated more than $471,000 in ill-gotten gains during t=
he course of the scheme.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well,=
 he allegedly violated the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/25195151.265551/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydG=
ljbGVzLzIwMTgtMDgtMTIvdGhlLTEwLWxhd3Mtb2YtaW5zaWRlci10cmFkaW5n/607f07ceef4b=
8524a319a23cCc83e6980" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">Fourth Law of Insider Trading</a> (=E2=80=9Cdon=E2=80=99t do i=
t in your mother=E2=80=99s account=E2=80=9D), but all in all it=E2=80=99s a=
 respectable effort. The SEC went out of its way to say that he was hard to=
 catch:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CDespite Sanche=
z=E2=80=99s alleged efforts to avoid detection by limiting the size of his =
trades and using four different accounts to trade under his parents=E2=80=
=99 names, the SEC=E2=80=99s keen analysis stitched together this pattern o=
f suspicious trading and exposed gross violations of duty by a compliance p=
rofessional who exploited the sensitive information he was hired to protect=
.=E2=80=9D said Joseph G. Sansone, Chief of the SEC=E2=80=99s Market Abuse =
Unit.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">How many other complianc=
e analysts out there are just a little bit better at covering their tracks?=
